Rationale: Fig. 4 shows that Mint1 is highly concentrated in the presynaptic membrane, particularly at the active zone.

22/6/2017 Pim;
Literal: "For the vast majority of synapses, immunolabeling of mint1 was highly concentrated in the presynaptic membrane, particularly at the active zone and to a lesser degree observed on SV as well in the presynaptic terminals (Fig. 4a,b). However, a very few synapses had significant immunoreactivity of mint1 in the postsynaptic density (PSD), but not in the presynaptic terminals (Fig. 4c). Among 200 synapses we looked over, one of them (0.5%) was postsynaptic-positive and the others were presynaptic-positive; no synapses were double-positive. Cytosol matrix and cytosolic surfaces of other membranous organelles such as mitochondria were not stained.". Experimental description: adult C57BL/6 mice
